=== TASK ===
# Booking Detail

## Overview
Develop a comprehensive Booking Detail module within the LuxeFlow CRM that presents a full, lifecycle-aware booking record. This page must render the entire booking story from quote to post-stay, including timeline stages, itinerary, resort & room category, rate details, commission structure, payment schedule, deadlines, supplier references, attachments, internal notes, and approval flows. The Booking Detail page must integrate smoothly with the Operations Command Center and with the Booking Lifecycle & Booking Management systems, providing actionable insights and inline handoffs. All UI must adhere to the project’s design system, performance, accessibility, and security requirements. All data access and UI rendering must be robust to null/undefined values, with strict runtime safety as described in the mandatory coding standards.

## Page Description (Full Detail)
What this page is:
- The Booking Detail page is the authoritative, read/write record for a single booking. It consolidates every aspect of the booking: client linkage, timeline (quote → confirmed → pre-arrival → in-stay → post-stay), itinerary items (days, activities, transfers with times), resort and room category, pricing (rates, currency, tax, fees), commission structure and calculated net, payment schedule (invoices, milestones, due dates, payment status), deadlines and SLA items, supplier references, attachments (contracts, terms, itineraries), internal notes, and approval/workflow states. It also presents downstream actions (send proposal, issue invoice, request approval, create task, link message) and inline handoffs to operations teams as required.

Connected features and UI goals:
- Operations Command Center integration: surface booking in 7-day upcoming stays, payment due items, overdue tasks, approvals needed, and urgent alerts related to this booking.
- Booking Lifecycle & Booking Management integration: reflect lifecycle stages in the timeline, enable editing of stages, adjust payment schedules, attach supplier references, and enable internal handoffs.
- Shared data integrity: pull client, resort, and supplier data from the core data layer; ensure referential integrity and synchronized state across modules.

UI elements and visual guidance (matching the Design System):
- Booking header: compact summary including Booking Reference, Status (with stage badge), Client name (with avatar), Resort, Room Category, Check-in/Check-out dates, Total value, Outstanding balance, and a quick action bar.
- Booking Timeline: horizontally laid out or vertical stacked stages showing quotes, confirmations, deadlines, pre-arrival events, in-stay milestones, and post-stay wrap-up. Each stage displays timestamp, responsible actor, and a quick status indicator. Allow inline edits to stage dates where allowed by business rules.
- Itinerary Section: per-day blocks with day number, date, activities, transfers, and transfer times. Support adding/removing/editing items and reordering days.
- Rates & Commission Panel: breakdown by rate plan, line-item pricing, currency, taxes/fees, discounting, commission model (percentage/fixed/tiered), calculated commission, and supplier net. Show historical vs current changes with audit trail.
- Payment Schedule: list of invoices/milestones with due dates, amounts, currencies, status (paid/unpaid/overdue), links to payment gateways or portals, and ability to generate new invoices or update payment status.
- Deadlines & SLA: deadlines related to approvals, document deliveries, and task due dates pulled from Operations Center.
- Supplier Info: supplier contacts, reference numbers, contract attachments, and ability to attach new references.
- Attachments: document gallery with preview, versioning, and download links; per-attachment comments or notes.
- Internal Notes & Handover: private notes visible to authorized roles, handover templates, and ability to assign/Handoff to team members.
- Approvals & Workflows: display current approval requests, status, history, and actions to approve/deny or escalate.
- Actions Bar: contextual actions like Send Proposal, Issue Invoice, Request Approval, Create Task, Link Message, and Quick Convert to Booking / Quote from the detail view.
- Visual cues: consistent use of stage badges, dividers, cards, and left-aligned content; emphasis on clean hierarchy and scannability.

Visual guidance (as requested):
- The page should convey luxury, clarity, and efficiency with generous whitespace, soft elevation, and restrained ornamentation. Cards with subtle shadows, soft borders, and olive-green accents for CTAs. Typography should favor an elegant serif for headings and a readable sans-serif for body text. Interactive elements should feature smooth transitions, accessible focus states, and clear affordances.

